$ perfmon.exe

`perfmon.exe` is a GUI tool to collect and view → Windows/Management-Instrumentation/Performance-Counters[Performance Counter] data.

The exeuctable launches → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/mmc_exe[MMC] with the Performance Monitor snap-in, which provides access to the Performance Monitor, Data Collector Sets, and Reports tools.

Show Resource view:
code {
C:\> perfmon /res
code }

Start the *System Diagnostic Data Collector Set* and then display a report of its results:
code {
C:\> perfmon /report
code }

Start the *reliability monitor*:  
code {
C:\> perfmon /rel
code }

Start the *performance monitor*:
code {
C:\> perfmon /sys
code }

`perfmon.exe` starts the → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/perfmon_msc[`perfmon.msc`] snap in.

